<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:ns5="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xml:id="members" xml:lang="en">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>members</refname>
        <refpurpose>returns a vector of indexes corresponding to the common values of two vectors
        </refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Calling Sequence</title>
        <synopsis>loc = members(a, b, highest)</synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Arguments</title>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>a</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>vector of numbers, polynomials, booleans or strings</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>b</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>vector of numbers, polynomials, booleans or strings</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>highest</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>scalar boolean</para>
                    <para>
                        %t => return last occurence of <literal>b</literal> elements in <literal>a</literal>
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        %f => return first occurence of <literal>b</literal> elements in <literal>a</literal>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            <literal>members(a, b, highest)</literal> returns a matrix of <literal>a</literal>'s size. <literal>loc(i, j)</literal> = linear
            index in <literal>b</literal> of the first (highest == %f), or the last (highest == %t)
            occurrence of <literal>a(i, j)</literal>. <literal>loc(i, j)</literal> returns zero if <literal>a(i, j)</literal> is not found.
            <literal>%inf</literal> and <literal>-%inf</literal> values are supported either in <literal>a</literal> or <literal>b</literal>, but not <literal>%nan</literal>.
        </para>
        <para>
            When <literal>a</literal> is a vector of doubles and <literal>b</literal> is a vector of doubles in strictly increasing order,
            <literal>dsearch(a, b, "d")</literal> is preferred over <literal>members(a, b, %f)</literal>.
        </para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
A = [1 8 4 5 2 1];
B = [9 7 4 2 1 4];

loc = members(A, B, %t)
// Returns [5 0 6 0 4 5] because the last occurrence in B of the third element of A (which is 4) is in sixth position

loc = members(A, B, %f)
// Returns [5 0 3 0 4 5] because the first occurrence in B of the third element of A (which is 4) is in third position
 ]]></programlisting>
    </refsection>
